719068f-a.title: Manhattan: Columbus Avenue - 66th Street (West)
719068f-a.text:
Columbus Ave., south from but not including West 66th Street, showing
W.P.A. employees removing car tracks. Broadway, partially shown on the
Nright, intersects this Ave. and forms two triangular plots, thereby the
appellation Lincoln Square by which this locality is known.
August 25, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
